node.text: women are sexualized from the moment they are children. they don‚Äôt even understand the meaning of sexy and already they‚Äôre hearing comments about their bodies. we‚Äôre taught that our bodies and how much we show of them define our worth. we‚Äôre taught to hate the widening of our hips, and our growing chests. we‚Äôre taught to cover up so we don‚Äôt tempt others. but why aren‚Äôt others taught to control themselves? to ask for consent? teach kids it is normal for their bodies to bloom and that they don‚Äôt need to be ashamed and cover up if they don‚Äôt want to. let them learn and understand consent. teach them adults should know it is wrong to sexualize a child, and they need to speak up if it happens. teach young people to learn to love their bodies and that their worth is not defined by how much of their skin is showing, nor what they are wearing.
